@startuml seq_15_vote_on_content
title Sequence Diagram: UC-15 Vote on Content

actor User
participant "User Web" as Frontend
participant "Vote Controller" as Controller
participant "Vote Service" as Service
participant "Target Repo" as TargetRepo
participant "Vote Repo" as VoteRepo

User -> Frontend: (1.1) Open a post or comment
User -> Frontend: (2.1) Choose Upvote or Downvote
User -> Frontend: (3.1) Submit the vote
Frontend -> Controller: (3.2) POST /api/votes {target_id, target_type, value}
Controller -> Service: (4.1) Submit vote request
Service -> TargetRepo: (4.2) Validate authentication and target type
TargetRepo --> Service: (4.3) Target is approved and visible

Service -> VoteRepo: (5.1) Load existing vote, if any
VoteRepo --> Service: (5.2) Existing vote state

alt New vote
    Service -> VoteRepo: (6.1) Create new vote record
else Change vote (Up to Down, Down to Up)
    Service -> VoteRepo: (6.2) Change vote record
else Remove vote (Click same button again)
    Service -> VoteRepo: (6.3) Remove vote record
end

Service -> TargetRepo: (7.1) Recalculate and update vote counts
TargetRepo --> Service: (7.2) New totals updated
Service --> Controller: (8.1) Updated vote totals
Controller --> Frontend: (8.2) 200 OK
Frontend --> User: (8.3) Update vote count UI
@enduml
